(33768, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Although not specifically identified in studies with tinidazole, the following drug interactions were reported for metronidazole, a chemically-related nitroimidazole. Therefore, these drug interactions may occur with tinidazole. The following drug interactions were reported for metronidazole, a chemically-related nitroimidazole and may therefore occur with tinidazole: Warfarin and other oral coumarin anticoagulants: Anticoagulant dosage may need adjustment during and up to 8 days after tinidazole therapy ( 7.1) Alcohol-containing beverages/preparations: Avoid during and up to 3 days after tinidazole therapy ( 7.1) Lithium: Monitor serum lithium concentrations ( 7.1) Cyclosporine, tacrolimus: Monitor for toxicities of these immunosuppressive drugs ( 7.1) Fluorouracil: Mo', 'DailyMed');
